## üîç What Lovable supports now

* Lovable allows **GitHub integration / export of code** so your project‚Äôs code is versioned and portable. ([Lovable Documentation][1])
* In their FAQ, they explicitly ask ‚ÄúCan I export my project and host it elsewhere?‚Äù ‚Äî the answer is **yes**. ([Lovable Documentation][2])
* There are video tutorials that show step-by-step how to export source code from Lovable to download locally. ([YouTube][3])
* One video titled *‚ÄúHow to Download Website Files From Lovable?‚Äù* shows connecting to GitHub then downloading the files locally. ([YouTube][4])
* Also, a Chrome extension ‚ÄúLovable.dev Project Downloader ‚Äì Export as ZIP (One Click)‚Äù claims to let you export the full project as a ZIP without using GitHub. ([Chrome Stats][5])

