## ‚úÖ Steps to download the Lovable project locally

Here‚Äôs a general procedure you can follow:

| Step | What to do                                      | Notes / Tips                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| ---- | ----------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1    | **Connect your Lovable project to GitHub**      | In Lovable, look for ‚ÄúEdit Code‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúGitHub Integration‚Äù or ‚ÄúTransfer to Repository.‚Äù This pushes your project code (frontend, backend, assets) to a GitHub repo. ([Lovable Documentation][1])                                                     |
| 2    | **Clone or Download from GitHub**               | Once the project is in GitHub, go to that repo ‚Üí **Code** ‚Üí **Download ZIP** or clone (`git clone <repo-url>`).                                                                                                                                   |
| 3    | **Open/run locally**                            | Navigate into the project folder on your machine and install dependencies (e.g. `npm install` or similar) then run the dev server (e.g. `npm run dev` or `npm start`) depending on the stack. The video tutorials show doing this. ([YouTube][6]) |
| 4    | **(Optional) Use the ZIP downloader extension** | If you don‚Äôt want to go via GitHub, try the ‚Äúlovable.dev project downloader‚Äù extension which claims to let you export the entire project as ZIP directly from Lovable. ([Chrome Stats][5])                                                        |

